==English==
===Alternative spellings===
*[[carling]]

===Etymology===
From Old Norse ''[[karling]]'', feminine of ''[[karl]]'' ‘carl’.

===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|/ˈkɑ:lɪn/}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# {{italbrac|chiefly Scotland}} A [[woman]]; a [[hag]] or [[witch]].
# {{nautical}} A piece of squared timber fitted fore-and-aft betweek the deck beams of a wooden ship to provide support for the deck planking.

